═══════════════════════════════════════════
CODE QUALITY RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
═══════════════════════════════════════════
1. Every component handles 3 states: loading (MUI Skeleton), error (inline with retry button), empty (illustrated empty state with action CTA)
2. No `any` types — strict TypeScript throughout
3. All forms use React Hook Form + Zod resolver — no uncontrolled inputs
4. All destructive actions require ConfirmDialog before executing
5. Images use next/image with lazy loading
6. Mobile breakpoints: sidebar collapses to bottom nav on <md, tables scroll horizontally
7. Error messages are human: "GPS blocked — tap here to enable location in browser settings" not "Error: permission denied"
8. Stats cards show real calculated values: "₹18,400 saved this month" (based on prevented fake check-ins at avg ₹300/day), not placeholder zeroes
9. Copy is product-specific throughout — never generic ("Kerala's most trusted geo-attendance tool" not "Welcome to our app")
10. No lorem ipsum anywhere — all text is real product copy

